## Practice Day 2

Today I gave a mock test for C Programming, and the result was not great — but it was important.

Here’s how it went:
• Attempted: 9 out of 20 questions
• Correct: 2
• Incorrect: 7
• Not attempted: 11
• Time taken: 25 minutes (out of 60)
• Score: -1
• Rank: 668/1000

Clearly, there’s a gap between understanding concepts and applying them under test conditions.

I rushed a few questions, made mistakes, and also lacked confidence to attempt more.

But this is exactly why mock tests matter — to show the reality.

Now I know what I need to improve:
• Better accuracy
• More practice (especially PYQs)
• Time management
• Confidence while attempting

Not a good score, but a very useful lesson.

I’ll keep improving from here.

